1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:03,600
Here's what science actually says about correlation vs causation.

2
00:00:03,600 --> 00:00:08,400
Just because two things happen together doesn't mean one causes the other.

3
00:00:08,400 --> 00:00:11,200
Take ice cream sales and shark attacks.

4
00:00:11,200 --> 00:00:13,200
They both spike in summer.

5
00:00:13,200 --> 00:00:15,600
But do they cause each other?

6
00:00:15,600 --> 00:00:19,200
Researchers note that correlation merely highlights relationships, not causation.

7
00:00:19,200 --> 00:00:21,600
Random factors could be at play.

8
00:00:21,600 --> 00:00:26,400
Understanding this helps prevent misleading conclusions about data, leading to better decisions.

9
00:00:26,400 --> 00:00:29,200
Want to dive deeper into data science?

10
00:00:29,200 --> 00:00:30,800
Hit that follow button!
